, including Micropteropus, Epomops, Hypsignathus, Nanonycteris), Plerotina (Plerotes), and Myonycterina (Myonycteris, Megaloglossus) in the Late Miocene; (b) among Epomops, Hypsignathus, and other species of Epomophorina at the Pliocene\u2013Pleistocene boundary; and (c) among Myonycteris species in the Early Pleistocene. Within the Epomophorini, Stenonycteris lanosus emerged first, suggesting that lingual echolocation may have appeared in the common ancestor of Epomophorini and Rousettini. Our analyses suggest that multiple events of mtDNA introgression occurred within the Epomophorus species complex during the Pleistocene.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Hassanin, Alexandre", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Bonillo, C\u00e9line", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tshikung, Didier", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pongombo Shongo, C\u00e9lestin", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pourrut, Xavier", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Kadjo, Blaise", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Nakoun\u00e9, Emmanuel", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Tu, Vuong Tan", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pri\u00e9, Vincent", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Goodman, Steven M.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Plio-Pleistocene", "Rousettinae", "lingual echolocation", "mitochondrial base composition", "mitochondrial introgression", "sub-Saharan Africa", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/f6e7d6fe39e51dfb703623db71b0b6cf", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/2ccd1bd9ba2a002918d72ee2f20454661ed4372912c36274fc7cdf3e354abde9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/RGCIW2DF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/RGCIW2DF", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/